The <a href="http://www.w3.org/2011/webappsec/">Web Application Security Working Group</a> has published a Working Draft of <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/2015/WD-epr-20150609/">Entry Point Regulation</a>. Entry Point Regulation aims to mitigate the risk of reflected cross-site scripting (XSS), cross-site script inclusion (XSSI), and cross-site request forgery (CSRF) attacks by demarcating the areas of an application which are intended to be externally referencable. A specified policy is applied on external requests for all non-demarcated resources. Learn more about the <a href="http://www.w3.org/Security/">Security Activity</a>.</p> <p><img src="https://www.w3.org/analytics/piwik/piwik.php?idsite=7&amp;rec=1&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2Fblog%2Fnews%2Farchives%2F4749%3Fpk_campaign%3Dfeed%26pk_kwd%3Dentry-point-regulation-draft-published&amp;action_name=Entry+Point+Regulation+Draft+Published&amp;urlref=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2Fblog%2Fnews%2Ffeed" style="border:0;width:0;height:0" width="0" height="0" alt="" /></p>
]]>
</content:encoded>
